dev/adr/ADR-0.8.11-filter-grammar-unification.md:5:desc: Unify the two SHIPPED filter surfaces — G4 `Predicate` (json-path predicates over canonical_nodes `body`, surfaced on `read.list`) and G10 `SearchFilter` (closed 4-field struct over vec0 metadata columns, surfaced on `search_filtered`) — into ONE typed `Filter` contract with TWO internal compilation backends (canonical_nodes/json_extract and vec0-metadata pre-KNN WHERE). Option A (HITL-decided): a single superset type that dispatches; NOT a thin adapter over two types. Total backend-dispatch with typed rejection — every predicate has a defined outcome (compiles to backend X, or typed-rejects with a stated reason) in EACH context; no silent fallback, no demotion of an indexed pre-KNN predicate to a slow post-KNN json_extract. Closes reserved-gap 37.
