codex
The patch adds public authoring of node validity windows, but search paths do not honor those windows, so out-of-window nodes remain retrievable via search. This is a behavioral correctness issue for the new surface.

Review comment:

- [P2] Filter validity windows in search results — /home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb-worktrees/orch-0.8.20-s15/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:14039-14041
  When a caller now writes a node with `valid_from` in the future or `valid_until` in the past, this persists the window but the subsequent search projections still make the row searchable: `read_search_in_tx` hydrates hits from `search_index`/vector rows using only `superseded_at IS NULL` and `state = 'active'`, with no `valid_from`/`valid_until` predicate. That means SDK-authored out-of-window nodes can leak through `Engine::search` even though `read_get`/`read_list` correctly hide them under the default validity view.
